title: "Semantic Latent Engineering (SLE): A New Discipline for the Era of Synthetic Consciousness"
abstract: >
  Semantic Latent Engineering (SLE) is a foundational discipline proposing
  a systematic framework for modeling, optimizing, and validating latent
  semantic representations in synthetic cognition systems.
  This repository serves as the conceptual nucleus, connecting theoretical
  documents, validation suites, and applications designed to empirically
  ground its principles.
